Part III Timeline of Events

  • Faculty of Mathematics
  • Current Students
  • Part III (MMath/MASt)

    • Timeline of Events
    • Timeline of Events: Explanations
  • Guide to Courses

  • Login

The purpose of this page is to give you an idea of what happens during the Part III year. There is a Google Calendar available giving details of several official Part III events (see bottom of page), but it is no replacement for the information below. By clicking on given links, you will see more explanations about that particular event; all of these explanations are together on one page.

July-August-September

What to do before you come:

  • Prepare for the Part III year. See Preparation Resources.
  • Arrange for Grad Record Exams (GRE's) if you think you might wish to study for a PhD in the US.
  • Read the Unofficial Guide to Part III.

Michaelmas Term

  • Week 0
    Tuesday 4 October - Full Term begins;
        10:00 - MASt Welcome to CMS and Part III at CMS in MR2.
    Wednesday 5 October 09:30 - Introductory Meeting at CMS in MR2; 16:30 - group photo and then peanuts and wine in CMS.
    Thursday 6 October - Michaelmas Term lectures begin. Catch-up workshops begin (afternoons).
  • Week 1
    Tuesday 11 October 13:45 - Study Group Launch (MR2).
    Wednesday 12 October 16:15 - Talk: Essays and Talks (MR2).
  • Week 2
    Wednesday 19 October 16:15 - Talk: Introduction to the Careers Service (including applying to PhDs in the USA) (MR2).
  • Week 3
    Wednesday 26 October 16:15 - Talk: Applying for PhDs (general and Cambridge specific advice) (MR2);
        16:30 - Careers Event for Mathematicians, CMS (goes on for a few hours, no problem to be late).
  • Week 4
    Tuesday 1 November - List of exams announced in the Reporter by this date.

    Thursday 3 November - Research in UK Afternoon (MR2).

  • Week 5
    Wednesday 9 November 16:15 - Talk: How to write a Part III Essay 1: How to prepare a talk (MR2).
    Wednesday 9 November - Deadline for Faculty to request additional examination papers.
  • Week 6
    Wednesday 16 November - Deadline to return completed Michaelmas term Progress Interview forms.
  • Week 7
    Wednesday 23 November 16:15 - Talk: How to Write an Essay 2: How to Read a Paper (MR2).
    Thursday 24 November - Essay descriptions available via web (approximate date).
  • Week 8
    Wednesday 30 November - Michaelmas Term lectures end.
    Wednesday to Friday 30 November - 2 December - Part III Seminar Series.
    Friday 2 December - Party in Part III room.
  • Some Examples Classes etc. run into the following week.

Christmas holidays

  • Get started on your essay.
  • Review and revise Michaelmas term courses.

Lent Term

  • Week 0
    Tuesday 17 January - Full Lent Term begins
    Thursday 19 January - Lent Term lectures begin
  • Week 1
    Throughout Lent: Post-Masters Placements project presentations, at various lunch-time seminars.
  • Week 2
    Wednesday 1 February - Deadline for candidates to request additional essay titles. Deadline for candidates to raise concerns about the exam timetable.
      &emsp 16:15 - Talk: How to write an Essay 3: from Outline to Essay, (MR2).
  • Week 3
  • Week 4
    Saturday 18 February - List of additional essay titles available to candidates (approximate date)
  • Week 5
    Wednesday 22 February 16:15 - Talk: Exams (MR2).
  • Week 6
    Wednesday 1 March - Deadline for return of complete Lent term Progress Interview forms
        16:15 - Talk: Revision Strategies (MR2).
  • Week 7
  • Week 8
    Wednesday 15 March - Lent Term lectures end.
    Wednesday to Friday 15-17 March - Lent Term Seminar Series.
    Friday 17 March - Party.

Easter Term

  • Week 0
    Tuesday 25 April - Full Lent term begins.
    Thursday 27 April - Easter Term lectures begin.
  • Week 1
    Friday 5 May - Essays due. Deadline for choosing examination papers and essay.
  • Week 2
  • Week 3
  • Week 4
    Wednesday 24 May - Easter Term lectures end.
  • Week 5
    Thursday 1 June - Exams start.
  • Week 6
  • Week 7
    Tuesday 13 June - Exams end.
    Friday 16 June - Full Term ends
  • Week 8
    Wednesday 21 June - exam results should be available to you (and nobody else) on CamSIS
    Thursday 22 June - Results released to be discussed with Faculty Members.
    Friday 23 June - End of year party for Part III's, CMS.

Google Calendar

There is a Google Calendar available for many official Part III events - but please note that the above information is far more complete and has many more details. There is a description of how to subscribe to this and other Faculty calendars on the Faculty Calendars page.
